      "code": "PX511502",
      "abbreviation": "PX511502",
      "description": "The Alcohol and Cannabis Simultaneous Use Scale (ACSUS) is a self-administered questionnaire. Respondents answer nine questions about simultaneous alcohol and cannabis use frequency, quantity, and impact.",
      "domain": "Substance Use",
      "citation": "Shipley, J. L., & Braitman, A. L. (2024). Assessment of simultaneous alcohol and cannabis use and its related consequences and cognitions in college students: A narrative review. Alcohol: Clinical and Experimental Research, 48 (2), 230-240. [PhenX: https://www.phenxtoolkit.org/protocols/view/511502]",
